Substance is correct — Cargo does set that env var to the absolute path of the freshly-built binary. **One grammar fix:** missing "is" — `whose value the full path` should be `whose value is the full path`.

Cleaner version:

```rust
/// Build a `Command` invoking the `vc-x1` binary that Cargo built
/// for this test crate. Cargo sets `CARGO_BIN_EXE_vc-x1` to the
/// full path of the freshly-built binary; this `Command` runs it.
```

Or keeping closer to your shape:

```rust
/// Build a `Command` invoking the `vc-x1` binary that Cargo built
/// for this test crate. Cargo sets `CARGO_BIN_EXE_vc-x1` whose
/// value is the full path to the vc-x1 it built and we will
/// subsequently run.
```

Either works. The first is tighter; the second preserves your phrasing with the missing "is" added.

